author: PiegeonWP
body:
It's OK to be suspicious but the fact of the matter is China Rapid Finance was a real company and listed on the NYSE for years. After approval from shareholders, the decision was made to change the name to SOS Limited, better aligning with the core business and  parent company. 

A few key names helping the case for SOS....

Russell Krauss - Vice Chair, Board Member.
 ** I won't provide the link to his LinkedIn page. You are all free to check that yourself. However, he was an executive at Hewlett Packard for many years. Also previous ties to Westinghouse and Electronic Data Systems.

Douglas Brown - Independent, Non Executive Director
**Former Morgan Stanley executive for years and now part of the Transamerica leadership team. He is listed on their official site and as part of his bio, notes he is an investor in China Rapid Finance.
https://www.transamerica.com/individual/why-transamerica/who-we-are/leadership/



Say what you want about the viability of the operation, but these guys are vetted and certainly help the case for SOS.
